en't you the one who was bragging about selling four parchments you claimed nbg on?  I heard something to this effect when I was grouped in Valor a few days ago...kinda funny. Now that you have your spells, you want to go ffa roll.<br>
<br>
Now, back to the subject:<br>
<br>
First, let's talk about spectrals and etherals.  I hate to break this to ya, but the majority of the server is gonna end up getting spectrals the same way they got KEI - from the top guilds.  If I had a spectral parchment, and someone offered me 4 etherals for it, I'd tell them to buzz off.  Spectrals are from mobs up two or three tiers.  As it is right now, most guilds will never see most of tier two.  So get ready for paying out the colon for your 63+ spells.<br>
<br>
Now, on the topic of duplicate spells, you would need someone to run and do the turn in, and then be honest about what they got.  That means leaving the group.  Um, yeah, I want my shaman gone for 20 mins or so to do the turn in.  I want my cleric to run off and leave us sitting there while he does his turn in.  I'd rather we kept killing.<br>
<br>
As far as a melee demanding to roll on parchments in a group where even one caster is lacking his 61-62 spells...I think you'd be looking for a new group, or having an inordinate amount of deaths.  Especially if it's the cleric or slower who need the spell.  Asking to roll on parchments is like casters asking to roll on plate bps that drop in Kael.  If you're wearing better, fine.  But if you're standing there in a treeweave...  Because that's what you'd be doing in a group where any caster in it needs even one of thier level 61/62 spells.<br>
<br>
The best way to avoid bad feelings is to find out what the loot rules are when you are invited to the group.  If you have a problem with them, don't join.  It's not that hard, honestly.   It's funny, but the only case I've had where loot has been a problem in PoP was from a shaman bitching because the mob we were planning on killing dropped parchments and items, and all the casters except him agreed to roll on parchments only and let the melee split the droppable loot among themselves if both dropped;  he wanted to be able to roll on the droppable items if they were shaman usable as well.  Well, we got ganked, and only had one item drop, which everyone rolled on, per agreement.. but goddamn, if you're gonna ask melee to sit out on something, your ass has to sit out on stuff too.  <br>
<br>
Jerry's Final Thoughts:  FFS, stop looking at your bank account when a piece of loot drops.  Be glad that something dropped that might give someone their last spell so they can stop worrying about the damn parchments.  Believe it or not, casters hate the parchments as much as melee do.  They'd much rather get their damn spells, than a duplicate that they can sell for 30k. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lonagan>lonagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/21/02 11:52:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2260.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposal: Ethereal Parchments to go Open Roll from 18th?</span><hr size=1>   /agree, this is much better here than on the FB, seeing as how we have actually discussed something ina clear rational manner.<br>
<br>
  The only distinction I would draw with the Kael armor drops situation is that plate/ chain/ leather/ silk pieces drop relatively evenly, so its a lot easier to just roll on what you can wear.  But to take it a step further, lets say you are in an arena group and plate legs drop.  All plate classes already have them.  What do you do then?  Do the plate classes still just roll on them?  No, everyone does to get them to MQ.  I would say the chief difference is that there is balanced loot in Kael.  If  say &quot;ethereal armor pieces&quot; or &quot;ethereal stat upgrades&quot; dropped that we could turn in for a random piece of armor or stat boost, in addition to parchments, then i would be perfectly happy letting casters have all the parchments, because that would not be the only loot.  Unfortuneately, SOE in their infinite wisdom figured that having ONLY caster loot drop in the PoP zones that 90% of people hunt in would be fine.  <br>
<br>
  Whether you like it or not, if you say that all parchments should go to spell weilding classes, then you are saying pure melees should get no loot.  Biased though I may be playing a warrior who XPs primarily in PoP, I see something patently unjust in the statement that any class should not get loot.  And what of the compromise?  What of parchments going to casters first and then melees in a group?  People havn't commented on that very much.  Is even a compromise (that STILL gives favoritism to spell classes) too much to suggest? <p>  Kazak- 57 Troll Warrior.<br>
<br>
  Arabis- 40  Wood Elf Druid.<br>
<br>
  Few things are more enraging to people than to have their identity or their sense of home stripped away.  They will fight for it, kill for it, sing for it, write poetry for it and novelize about it.   Because without a sense of home and belonging, life becomes barren and rootless.  And life as a tumbleweed is no life at all.<br>
