-Thomas Friedman, The Lexus and the Olive Tree</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=unnone>Unnone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/21/02 1:11:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2260.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposal: Ethereal Parchments to go Open Roll from 18th?</span><hr size=1> Your plate legs analogy is flawed.  If everyone has their 61-62 spells, then everyone should get to roll on the parchments, since all it is at that point is a cash item.  There is no 'need' at that point by any member of the group for the parchment, except as a cash/trade item, and it should go to a free roll.  You're avoiding the fact that if you didn't have plate legs, and a caster asked to roll on them, you'd hit the roof.<br>
<br>
Yes, people can lie about this.  Just like people put on crap gear when they go to groups so they can claim nbg on stuff.   I have personally seen a warrior claim nbg on a lore sword that he was not wielding and could not loot - BUSTED TO THE MAX. There are liars and swindlers all over.<br>
<br>
But, like it or not, ethereal parchments are caster loot.  You said that you can see rolling on plate legs when everyone in the group has Kael/Tov/better legs.  As long as one caster in the group does not have all his level 61-62 spells, if you demand to roll on the parchments that he would use, you have shown yourself to be a hypocrite.<br>
<br>
Am I saying that pure melee should get no loot?  No.  I'm saying melee should not get caster loot, if a caster can use it.  Just like melee shouldn't get caster loot.  If that means you don't get phat platz, buy a tissue.  Because you're saying melee should get to roll on the equivalent of velious silk armor, at a time when not everyone is geared up.  You're saying warriors should get to roll against wizards on the gnarled staff from Venril.  You see the spells selling for 20k, and think &quot;I could get me some of that.&quot;  You don't see the casters taking that 20k and buying spells from each other.  You don't see people grouping and grinding for hours on end hoping to get that last parchment, that last spell.  <br>
<br>
Let me ask you this, Kazak.   You're in a shroom king group.  You decide not to wait on the king to pop, and to break up.  Just then, the puller brings a jugg or two to your camp.  The shaman slows them;  you kill it.  It drops Malo.  That's the only loot that has dropped all night.  You know the shaman doesn't have Malo.  You know you're going to break up.  Do you want to roll on Malo?<br>
<br>
Now you're going to post how that isn't the same, how you can get loot for melee in the shroom king camp, and how it's not guaranteed that you'd get Malo from a parchment turn in.  Don't bother.  Just answer the question.<br>
<br>
Me, I'm betting you would want to.  Because if you wouldn't, then you're being inconsistent.  Why would you not roll on one spell, and then roll on another?  Because that's all a parchment is.  <br>
<br>
Here's another scenario for you.  Imagine if all your disciplines came from 'ethereal training manual' drops, and you're missing defensive.  An ethereal training manual drops.  Then a 65 enchanter with a full spell book wants to roll on it, saying he could trade that for a new ring that would give him 10 more mana.  How would you feel?<br>
<br>
That's the same thing you're doing.  Warrior abilities are given to them.  Hell, you got shield as a freebie, rather than an AA.  Think on that, while you moan about how you're not getting rich off of parchments.  And yeah, you're gonna talk about how weapons to a warrior are like spells to a caster.  Hogwash.  Weapons to a warrior are like flowing thought/mana items to casters, not like spells.  They increase your performance; they don't give you new abilities that make you or break you as a tank.  A warrior without a Blade of Carnage and an SoD is still a warrior with defensive and shield.  A chanter or bard without a decent level mez is a hurting puppy, when adds hit for 400, 500, 600, or 750.  <br>
<br>
If you have a severe need to see large amounts of platinum in your bank, demand a larger share of the sellibles.  Lots of the random stuff that drops from mobs sells for 80pp or higher.  Give the casters some for dots, and split the cash among the rest of the melee.  But keep your greedy 'I want phat lewtz' hands off the parchments that you want to fatten your bank when there is a caster in the group sitting there cursing each mob that doesn't drop a parchment.  Yup, you're not getting spell loot.  If you  really don't like it, don't go to the planes of power.  Nothing drops there for you.  I'm sure the xp in umbral is just fine at 57, and melee loot drops there as well.  I'm sure your guild would have people around your level hunting there.  By the way, what guild are you in?  I'm sure they'd be interested in your stance on this issue.  The casters especially. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/21/02 3:41:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2260.topic&index=63>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.aus-1.au.nu/images/photo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposal: Ethereal Parchments to go Open Roll from 18th?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Hey, Hogfather, aren't you the one who was bragging about selling four parchments you claimed nbg on? I heard something to this effect when I was grouped in Val