I doubt any 60+, or maybe even 55+ tank would agree with that statement.  A 60+ Warrior fighting in the Planes would be laughed out of any group if s/he came trotting along with a Lamentation and a Centi Short Sword.  I'd like to see a level 60 Warrior dual wielding Lamentations tank C4 in CT.  Hello dead casters.  Weapons for melees are just as important as spells for casters.  How many Rogues do you see running around Tier 2 PoP zones with a Crystalline Spider Fang?  Be serious.<br>
<br>
The fairest way to distribute loot in pick up groups is to let everyone roll for everything.  I'm not talking about what is desired or best for all, simply what is fair.  Is it not the fairest to let every person have an equal chance to win somehting?  NBG is a good idea in practice and makes some feel all warm and fuzzy but objectively there's no argument that can justify it being the &quot;fairest way&quot;.  Between friends it's a whole different can of worms obviously.<br>
<br>
Moot point from my perspective since I never do pickup groups for this very reason.  Stick to those you know and trust and there's never an issue.<br>
