<br>
What do you join a group for? Loot or exp? or both? Throughout the history of EQ, great exp spots may drop only caster items, or only melee items, very rarely both. Both melees and casters (casters being the overwhelming majority) have had to deal with this. Now that caster spells which are traditionally store bought and in most cases quite common become semi rare drops off exp group mobs, melees finaly have to deal with what casters have put up with for the past 3 years--having no useable loot on many good exp spots.<br>
<br>
Lets look at history a bit further. Traditionally, the groups who arrive at a new camp area mostly operate on a NBG system. The first FBSS went to melees, as did the first Lam, RBG, SBC etc etc. These first ones knew the value of these items, yet they used NBG in pickup groups because it made sense. Usually NBG continues until the rabble moves in, and then every wants to roll on everything to sell for pp.<br>
<br>
It's a pretty sad cycle, really.<br>
